# Clean Architecture Enforcement

Apply this quality gate to every non-trivial change set.
Use `system-architecture-blueprint.mdc` and `router-service-boundaries.mdc` as canonical architecture rules.

- Check for architectural drift in touched flows (duplicated logic, bloated routers/views, parallel implementations).
- Keep shared-first behavior: reuse existing abstractions before adding new ones.
- Keep boundaries thin: transport in routers/views, business logic in services/hooks.
- If decomposition opportunities are found, propose explicit change stories before broad refactors.
